Perfect! Now that @bitnoi.se/react-scheduler is installed successfully, here’s how to use it step by step:

✅ 1. Import the Scheduler in your component
In any component where you want the calendar (e.g. Calendar.jsx), add:

jsx
Copier
Modifier
import React from 'react';
import Scheduler from '@bitnoi.se/react_scheduler';
import '@bitnoi.se/react_scheduler/dist/style.css'; // Optional: If styles are provided
Make sure this path is correct. If there's no style.css, check the dist/ folder or use custom styles.

✅ 2. Basic Usage Example
Here's a simple working version inside Calendar.jsx:

jsx
Copier
Modifier
import React from 'react';
import Scheduler from '@bitnoi.se/react_scheduler';
import '@bitnoi.se/react_scheduler/dist/style.css'; // If available

export default function CalendarPage() {
  return (
    <div style={{ padding: '2rem' }}>
      <h2>Calendrier des tâches</h2>
      <Scheduler />
    </div>
  );
}
✅ 3. Routing to the Calendar
If you're using react-router-dom, make sure to route to this page:

jsx
Copier
Modifier
import CalendarPage from './components/Calendar'; // or wherever your file is

<Routes>
  <Route path="/calendar" element={<CalendarPage />} />
</Routes>
And in your navbar or any link:

html
Copier
Modifier
<a href="/calendar">Calendrier</a>
✅ 4. Check Output
Run the app: npm run dev

Go to http://localhost:5173/calendar

You should see the scheduler/calendar component

If it shows up blank:

Open the browser dev console and check for any errors

Check if you see any missing CSS warnings or import issues

Let me know and I’ll help debug

